{
  "texts": [
    "For the neural networks, the trends mirror those observed for higher-mass halos: vipr consistently delivers the best performance, closely followed by copra.",
    "Both models maintain high accuracy and completeness within R Lag and experience only moderate declines beyond it, with vipr showing the most stable behavior.",
    "In stark contrast, pinocchio performs poorly across the entire radial range for these lowmass objects.",
    "Its completeness is significantly reduced even well inside R Lag, and its purity is already degraded at small radii before dropping steeply outside the halo boundaries.",
    "These results emphasize the increasing difficulty of the perturbation-theory-based model in correctly identifying and classifying low-mass proto-halos."
  ]
}